As an API user, we need to support filtering on the list of Catalogs API. These filter options should support filter by Status, and date range on the lastUpdatedDate field. status - APPROVED, PUBLISHED lastUpdatedDate - range                                  fromDate -                                    toDate - Technical Details: Add support for the following filtering options on the Catalogs GET API   /catalogs Add filtering by  Status , All Catalog Status can be passed as filters Support single status and multiple status, when providing multiple status, separate them by comma(,) If wrong value is provided in the status, there should be a validation error ignore the comma at the end of the filter e.g APPROVED and APPROVED, should result in same result APPROVED, PUBLISHED should filter all the catalogs in APPROVED and PUBLISHED status, the results are sorted by lastUpdatedDate Added filtering by lastUpdatedDate, when providing the filter by this date, there should be two fields to provide the date range, We already have the field  lastUpdatedAfter  exposed in the API, we need additional  lastUpdatedBefore . When providing the filter options, all the fields are optional. Id dates are provided than the following conditions should be considered only lastUpdatedAfter is provided in the filters, Return all results after this date, if the date is provided in date only format, consider the time of end of the day, e.g 01/29/2024 is provided than filter all records after 01/29/2024 t 00:00:00.000  only lastUpdatedBefore is provided in the filters, Return all results before this date, if the date is provided in date only format, consider the time of start of the day, e.g 01/29/2024 is provided than filter all records after 01/29/2024 t 00:00:00.000 If both the dates are provided than consider the records between provided date ranges. If the date are provided in date only format, consider the following rule (lastUpdateAfter - lastUpdatedBefore). e.g  01/27/2024 t 00:00:00.000 - 01/29/2024 t 00:00:00.000 will filter all the records from the 01/28/2024 If the fields are provided in wrong format, than we need to provide use with validation error, end date cannot be before start date.  the result will be empty, since there is nothing in the provided range e.g selecting (lastUpdateAfter - lastUpdatedBefore). e.g 01/29/2024 t 00:00:00.000 - 01/27/2024 t 23:59:59.999 will return no result as there is nothing in between these dates (One suggestion could be to give a validation error, since this is not a correct date range.) Sort by should be by the last updated date field. Update the Vroozi API documentation to expose these additional query parameters. Dates should be accepted in the supported formats. Testing from Swagger UI and Postman should be performed. Error Messages When we provide the invalid operator  {
